{"body": [{"indent": 0, "text": ["VDB from Polygons"], "type": "title", "extent": [103, 125], "level": 0}, {"indent": 0, "type": "summary", "extent": [125, 215], "text": ["Converts polygonal surfaces and/or surface attributes into VDB volume primitives."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [16, 105], "text": ["See ", {"text": ["volumes"], "fullpath": "/model/volumes", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/model/volumes"}, " for an explanation of standard volumes and OpenVDB volumes."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [245, 378], "text": ["The input geometry must be a quad or triangle mesh.\n    This node will \"convex\" the input surface into such a mesh if it isn\u2019t."]}], "indent": 0, "role": "item", "type": "note", "extent": [239, 245]}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "note_group"}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [378, 474], "text": ["This node can create a distance field (signed (SDF) or unsigned) and/or a density (fog) field."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [474, 653], "text": ["When you create a fog field you can choose to fill the band of voxels on the surface or (if you have an airtight surface) fill the surface (see the ", {"text": ["Fill interior"], "type": "ui"}, " parameter)."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [653, 840], "text": ["Since VDB primitives only store the voxels around the surface, they can have a much a higher effective resolution than creating a traditional volume with ", {"text": ["IsoOffset"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/isooffset", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/isooffset"}, "."]}, {"indent": 0, "type": "para", "extent": [840, 981], "text": ["You can connect a VDB to the second input to automatically use that VDB\u2019s orientation and voxel size (see the ", {"text": ["Reference VDB"], "type": "ui"}, " parameter)."]}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1026, 1150], "text": ["The size of voxels in the output VDB volume.\n    Surface features smaller than this will not be in the output VDB."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Voxel Size"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "voxelsize"}, "extent": [993, 1006], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1185, 1338], "text": ["If the second input is connected, you can enter the name of a VDB primitive in the second input to copy the orientation and voxel size from it."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1338, 1390], "text": ["See ", {"fragment": "#group", "text": ["specifying volumes"], "value": "/model/volumes#group", "fullpath": "/model/volumes#group", "scheme": null, "type": "link"}, "."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Reference VDB"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "group"}, "extent": [1150, 1165], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1404, 1565], "text": ["Creates a signed distance field (SDF).\n    An SDF stores the distance to the surface in each voxel.\n    (If the voxel is inside, the distance is negative.)"]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Distance VDB"], "role": "item", "extent": [1390, 1404], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1574, 1767], "text": ["Creates a density field.\n    Voxels in the band on the surface store ", {"text": ["1"], "type": "code"}, " and voxels outside store ", {"text": ["0"], "type": "code"}, ".\n    The size of the filled band is controlled with the ", {"text": ["Interior Band Voxels"], "type": "ui"}, "."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1767, 1875], "text": ["Turn on ", {"text": ["Fill interior"], "type": "ui"}, " to create a solid VDB from an airtight surface instead of a narrow band."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Fog VDB"], "role": "item", "extent": [1565, 1574], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [1895, 2095], "text": ["You can generate additional VDB primitives that store the values of primitive (face), point, or vertex ", {"text": ["attributes"], "fullpath": "/model/attributes", "scheme": null, "type": "link", "value": "/model/attributes"}, ".\n    Only voxels in the band around the surface will be set."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Surface Attributes"], "role": "item", "extent": [1875, 1895], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2106, 2187], "text": ["The name of point, vertex, or primitive attribute to create a VDB from."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Attribute"], "role": "item", "extent": [2095, 2106], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2228, 2354], "text": ["A new name for the generated VDB primitive storing the attribute values.\n    Leave this blank to use the attribute name."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["VDB Name"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "attributevdbname"}, "extent": [2187, 2197], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2389, 2435], "text": ["How vector values should be interpreted."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Vector Type"], "role": "item", "attrs": {"id": "vectype"}, "extent": [2354, 2367], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2461, 2621], "text": ["Sets whether ", {"text": ["Exterior band"], "type": "ui"}, " and ", {"text": ["Interior band"], "type": "ui"}, " are specified in Houdini units.\n    When this option is off, the band width parameters are in voxels."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Use World Space for Band"], "role": "item", "extent": [2435, 2461], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2643, 2757], "text": ["How many voxels outside the surface to fill in the generated VDB (when ", {"text": ["Use world space for band"], "type": "ui"}, " is off)."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Exterior Band Voxels"], "role": "item", "extent": [2621, 2643], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2772, 2892], "text": ["How many Houdini units outside the surface to fill in the generated VDB (when ", {"text": ["Use world space for band"], "type": "ui"}, " is on)."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Exterior Band"], "role": "item", "extent": [2757, 2772], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [2914, 3027], "text": ["How many voxels inside the surface to fill in the generated VDB (when ", {"text": ["Use world space for band"], "type": "ui"}, " is off)."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Interior Band Voxels"], "role": "item", "extent": [2892, 2914], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3042, 3107], "text": ["The distance to compute the distance field inside the mesh."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Interior Band"], "role": "item", "extent": [3027, 3042], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3122, 3379], "text": ["In SDF mode, Fill Interior extends the signed value all the way to the middle of the volume. In Fog mode, a gradient is applied from 0 at the surface (0 values of the SDF) to 1 at the innermost distance of the SDF Field (the most negative SDF values)."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Fill Interior"], "role": "item", "extent": [3107, 3122], "type": "parameters_item"}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3404, 3622], "text": ["When creating a ", {"text": ["Distance VDB"], "type": "ui"}, ", simply store the distance from the voxel to the surface (no negative values).\n    This avoids trying to figure out inside and outside, so the surface doesn\u2019t need to be airtight."]}, {"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3622, 3711], "text": ["This is similar to the Minimum function of the ", {"text": ["Iso Offset SOP"], "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/isooffset", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/isooffset"}, "."]}], "indent": 0, "text": ["Unsigned Distance Field"], "role": "item", "extent": [3379, 3404], "type": "parameters_item"}], "container": true, "role": "item_group", "type": "parameters_item_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Parameters", "role": "section", "extent": [981, 993], "container": true, "type": "parameters_section", "id": "parameters"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3747, 3786], "text": ["The polygonal surface to convert."]}], "indent": 0, "type": "dt", "extent": [3719, 3747], "text": ["Polygonal mesh to convert"]}, {"body": [{"indent": 4, "type": "para", "extent": [3810, 3913], "text": ["If connected, this node copies the orientation and voxel size from a VDB primitive in this input."]}], "indent": 0, "type": "dt", "extent": [3786, 3810], "text": ["Optional reference VDB"]}], "container": true, "type": "dt_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Inputs", "role": "section", "extent": [3711, 3719], "container": true, "type": "inputs_section", "id": "inputs"}, {"body": [{"body": [{"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [3922, 3940], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/vdb", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/vdb"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [3940, 3970], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/vdbfromparticles", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/vdbfromparticles"}]}, {"indent": 0, "blevel": 2, "type": "bullet", "extent": [3970, 3994], "text": [{"text": "", "fullpath": "/nodes/sop/isooffset", "scheme": "Node", "type": "link", "value": "/nodes/sop/isooffset"}]}], "container": true, "type": "bullet_group"}], "indent": 0, "level": 1, "text": "Related", "role": "section", "extent": [3913, 3922], "container": true, "type": "related_section", "id": "related"}], "title": ["VDB from Polygons"], "summary": ["Converts polygonal surfaces and/or surface attributes into VDB volume primitives."], "attrs": {"version": null, "tags": "create, model", "namespace": null, "internal": "vdbfrompolygons", "context": "sop", "type": "node", "icon": "SOP/vdbfrompolygons"}, "included": ["/nodes/sop/volume_types"], "type": "root"}